text.tspan: Figure 2. Model fits and individual level viral load measurements of untreated individuals.
(A) Model fits (black line) to viral loads (VL, log10) of 52 non-hospitalized untreated individuals (green dots). The asterisk denotes the
reported day of symptom onset. The horizontal dashed line represents the detection threshold (DT) of the RT-qPCR method to detect viral
load within the sample (DT = 2.1 log10 VL). Dots on the dashed line denote negative test results, likely measurements below the DT.
(B) Model fits (black line) to viral loads (log10) of 17 hospitalized untreated individuals (blue dots). The day of hospitalization is highlighted
by a vertical dotted line. Symbols same as in (A).
